## Aggregate Formulas (Verified)

### NUST
Aggregate = (Matric% × 0.10) + (FSc% × 0.15) + (NET% × 0.75)
- NET is out of 200 → convert to percentage before applying

### FAST (Computing/Business)
Aggregate = (Matric% × 0.10) + (FSc% × 0.40) + (Test% × 0.50)
- Test can be NU Test or NAT

### UET Lahore
Aggregate = (Matric% × 0.25) + (FSc% × 0.45) + (ECAT% × 0.30)
- ECAT is out of 400 → convert to percentage before applying

### COMSATS
Aggregate = (Matric% × 0.10) + (FSc% × 0.40) + (NTS% × 0.50)

### Air University
Aggregate = (Matric% × 0.15) + (FSc% × 0.35) + (AU-CBT% × 0.50)

### Generic Formula Function Pattern
```python
def calculate_aggregate(matric_obtained, matric_total,
                         fsc_obtained, fsc_total,
                         test_obtained, test_total,
                         matric_weight, fsc_weight, test_weight) -> float:
    matric_pct = (matric_obtained / matric_total) * 100
    fsc_pct    = (fsc_obtained / fsc_total) * 100
    test_pct   = (test_obtained / test_total) * 100
    return (matric_pct * matric_weight) + (fsc_pct * fsc_weight) + (test_pct * test_weight)
```

